n most of the goods sold on Amazon, you need to pay an annual or monthly subscription fee. The fee varies depending on your country of residence, but it is almost irrelevant, as it is low and your savings are quickly earned with only 2-3 orders each month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-5-amazon-inspired-plugins-that-will-boost-your-sales/\">The Amazon marketing </a>department knew that unexpected shipping fees are the main cause of abandoned online carts and fixed the problem at its roots and turned it into a source of benefits for everybody, effectively <strong>turning a cost into a service.</strong><br />\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1141534\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1775\" height=\"883\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1.jpg 1775w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-300x149.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-1024x509.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-768x382.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-1536x764.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-500x249.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-440x219.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-261x130.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-311x155.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-363x181.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-270x134.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1775px) 100vw, 1775px\" /></p>\n<p>Besides from it being an almost passive source of income, it increases the average value of every single subscriber, since being able to use a free shipping service surely increases the number of sales.<br />\nThis is what every entrepreneur should do: Amazon isolated a problem and fixed it by making it its forte.</p>\n<p>Amazon Prime is probably the best and most popular example, so lets take a look at how we can copy this type of subscription. Yes, big shoes to fill, but lets break down what Amazon Prime actually offers.</p>\n<p>The perks of this subscription extend way beyond the free delivery and include some premium movies, music, and product discounts. To start off, we need to install a number of plugins to manage the free delivery and discounts on our products.</p>\n<p>Apart from WooCommerce, we will install:</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\">YITH WooCommerce Subscription </a></strong><br />\n<strong><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-membership/\">YITH WooCommerce Membership</a></strong><br />\n<strong><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-dynamic-pricing-and-discounts/\">YITH WooCommerce Dynamic Pricing and Discounts</a></strong></p>\n<p>The Save Marketplace is our store where we want to give our regular customers the possibility to save even more on delivery by offering an annual subscription of $29.99. The perk will be that they will receive 10% off on all grocery products.</p>\n<h2>Step 1 &#8211; Create a subscription product to take payment each year.</h2>\n<p>Without going through every subscription setting, which you can find in the documentation, we will create an annual plan for $29,99 with a 30-day free trial. No payment will be taken for the first 30 days.<br />\nGo to products, create new, and select a simple product with a tick in Subscriptions as it shows in the screenshot. You can further customize your payment settings.</p>\n<video id=\"video-802465_html5\" width=\"1140\" height=\"691\" loop=\"true\" autoplay=\"true\"  preload=\"metadata\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5a093bcfe148e954fb375795fb52c5d6.mp4\" style=\"width: 1140px; height: 691px;\"><source type=\"video/mp4\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5a093bcfe148e954fb375795fb52c5d6.mp4\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5a093bcfe148e954fb375795fb52c5d6.mp4\">https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5a093bcfe148e954fb375795fb52c5d6.mp4</a></video>\n<p>To make it look good and stand out, weve quickly added a pricing table using the YITH WooCommerce Subscription&#8217;s integrated blocks so we can get customers to sign up easily. We will create a link from every product page that allows for this discount when a user signs up.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1142622\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/81997cf5391a71259842d68255b1fd0c.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"421\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Step 2 &#8211; Create the membership for our Premium Customers which is linked to the subscription product.</h2>\n<p>This process is actually relatively simple, but dont underestimate the power of memberships. You can set up any rule for a page or product to be visible, partly visible, or hidden. So adding content that you want to use for a premium perk is all possible.</p>\n<p>Make sure that the membership is created when a certain product has been bought. In our case, the product Save Premium has been added.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1142720\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1536\" height=\"790\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1-300x154.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1-1024x527.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1-768x395.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1-500x257.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1-440x226.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1-261x134.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1-311x160.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1-363x187.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/01-1-270x139.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" /></p>\n<h2>Step 3 &#8211; Give the privileges and discounts to the premium customers</h2>\n<p>For that, we will need YITH WooCommerce Dynamic Pricing and Discounts.</p>\n<p>Firstly, lets set up the 10% discount by creating a category rule for all groceries.</p>\n<p>Choose Special offer, select Specific Product Categories, for which weve selected groceries</p>\n<p>Secondly, we added the discount for items in the basket and made sure this is only applicable to our Save Premium members.</p>\n<video id=\"video-802465_html5\" width=\"1140\" height=\"581\" loop=\"true\" autoplay=\"true\"  preload=\"metadata\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/a3c57ce546ac63f16a72443208a652b3.mp4\" style=\"width: 1140px; height: 581px;\"><source type=\"video/mp4\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/a3c57ce546ac63f16a72443208a652b3.mp4\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/a3c57ce546ac63f16a72443208a652b3.mp4\">https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/a3c57ce546ac63f16a72443208a652b3.mp4</a></video>\n<p>The next part is to ensure the premium customers get free shipping. You can do this straight using the WooCommerce shipping rules as this feature comes as part of the Membership plugin to be able to select &#8216;Membership Free Shipping&#8217;</p>\n<p>Go to WooCommerce Settings &gt; Shipping and select the shipping zones you want to apply this discount to and create a new shipping method if you havent done so yet.</p>\n<p>When creating a free shipping option for memberships, you need to make sure you simply select the option: Membership Free Shipping. Then save it After that, select which membership you want to associate with this option.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1142625\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"716\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping.jpg 2000w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-300x215.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-1024x733.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-768x550.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-1536x1099.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-500x358.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-440x315.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-261x187.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-311x223.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-363x260.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/free-shipping-270x193.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you have set up free shipping for your premium members! Create a customer account and test everything to make sure it works as you have intended. If you are unsure, check out the extensive documentation of each of the plugins or refer to this tutorial again.</p>\n<p>Here is an example product with a clear &#8216;call to action&#8217; on how potential members can save on this product. We think your customers will love this and become ever so loyal to your store.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1142676\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1840\" height=\"1277\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner.jpg 1840w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-300x208.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-1024x711.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-768x533.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-1536x1066.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-500x347.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-440x305.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-261x181.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-311x216.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-363x252.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/product-banner-270x187.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1840px) 100vw, 1840px\" /></p>\n<h3>Give your premium users more benefits.</h3>\n<p>Our example of copying Amazon Prime is just one of the options you can achieve with this combination of plugins. You can use this for many more scenarios in your store and give your most-valuable users more privileges for a regular subscription payment.</p>\n<p><strong>Example of Create your own robot magazine subscription.</strong></p>\n<p>Instead of using an annual subscription model, you can create a monthly membership plan with different payment tiers. The highest tier will get everything for free, whereas the middle tier would get a discount on some of the premium content. YITH WooCommerce Subscription allows the members to easily up or downgrade.</p>\n<p>Imagine you have a subscription to create your own mini robot. Each month the subscriber gets a box with materials sent and your tutorials are all available on your site but only visible to members. Furthermore, the subscribers can get a discount for a limited period whilst the subscription lasts, on other products. You can see that in this combination you can extend the different perks and make it a lot more attractive for new users to sign up and remain a subscriber for longer.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1142621\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"476\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox.jpg 1979w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-300x178.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-1024x609.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-768x457.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-1536x914.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-500x297.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-440x262.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-261x155.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-311x185.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-363x216.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/meatbox-270x161.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Example of a weekly supply of vegetables &#8211; with an additional discount on a meat box</strong></p>\n<p>The ever so popular subscription of grocery or vegetable boxes from your farm shop or regional supplier is here to stay but a big problem is the rate of cancellations of this subscription model. Customers might get fed up with the same selections or cancel due to a planned holiday and never restart it again.</p>\n<p>One way to loyalize the customer is to create an additional discount on other products like a weekly meat box or fresh milk delivered 3 times a week. By giving a discount on these products, you lock your customers in having to buy the vegetable box too. The chances of cancellation or looking for a better supplier have suddenly gone down tremendously. Even better would be to create recipes that are linked to these grocery boxes and your customers can cook new dishes, adding a new dimension to your membership plans.</p>\n<h3>But it doesnt stop there, invest in the future of your business.</h3>\n<p>There are more advantages to adopting a membership model. You create a more loyal customer basis with an increasing number of repeat purchases. You start to build up a customer database, a regular income and you have suddenly become a very attractive and valuable business. You might not think of it now, but watch the Dragons Den and see how the dragons value subscribers, growth, and a proven plan for future income. And what about your competition? Maybe you can collaborate with other businesses and create a joined membership plan?<br />\nThe ideas are unlimited and your creativity is the only thing that is holding you back. Feel free to share your idea in the comments section, as we love hearing about your business plans.</p>\n<h4>Useful resources</h4>\n<p>To create a demo, start the subscriptions demo sandbox and enable the membership and dynamic pricing plugins. <a href=\"https://plugins.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\">Start here&gt;</a></p>\n<p><strong>Plugins</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\">YITH WooCommerce Subscription</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-membership/\">YITH WooCommerce Membership</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-dynamic-pricing-and-discounts/\">YITH WooCommerce Dynamic Pricing and Discounts</a></p>\n<p><strong>Plugin Documentation</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\">YITH WooCommerce Subscription Documentation</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-membership/\">YITH WooCommerce Membership Documentation</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-dynamic-pricing-and-discounts/\">YITH WooCommerce Dynamic Pricing and Discounts Documentation</a></p>\n<p><strong>Subscription Blog Posts</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/showcases/create-a-recurring-income-stream-using-woocommerce-subscriptions/\">Create a recurring income stream using WooCommerce Subscriptions</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/subscriptions-2-0-new-features-and-improvements-for-this-key-plugin/\">Subscriptions 2.0 new features and improvements </a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-amazon-prime-service/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"Version 2.0 of our Auction plugin for WooCommerce will make your jaw drop\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:109:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/version-2-0-of-our-auction-plugin-for-woocommerce-will-make-your-jaw-drop/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:117:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/version-2-0-of-our-auction-plugin-for-woocommerce-will-make-your-jaw-drop/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 14 Aug 2020 15:47:58 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"YITH News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=1142002\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:359:\"Among the many plugin updates that weve released, YITH Auction for WooCommerce is absolutely the most noteworthy. While we were updating the plugin demo with the newly added options, we ended up wondering: What options was the plugin actually offering before the update? Actually, it was a good plugin with always positive feedback from its [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Ausilia\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24907:\"<p>Among the many plugin updates that weve released, <strong>YITH Auction for WooCommerce</strong> is absolutely the most noteworthy.</p>\n<p>While we were updating the plugin demo with the newly added options, we ended up wondering:</p>\n<blockquote><p>What options was the plugin actually offering <em>before the update</em>?</p></blockquote>\n<p>Actually, it was a good plugin with always positive feedback from its users.</p>\n<p>But, lets face it, its a quality product now taken to the next level.</p>\n<p>A level that we found in no other auction plugin for WooCommerce that weve been analyzing in the past months.</p>\n<p>Because of the new UX that will make it even easier to create and handle auctions of any type, and because of the many new functionalities that weve integrated. From today on, it is possible to create sealed auctions and reverse auctions (where its the lowest bid that wins), as well as asking users to pay a fee before they can bid and check &#8211; if using our YITH Stripe plugin &#8211; if they have added a valid credit card as a payment method before their bid can be accepted.</p>\n<p>Below you find the main awesome features of <strong>YITH Auction for WooCommerce 2.0</strong>.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>1- The new UX</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142004\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1636\" height=\"1476\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1.jpg 1636w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-300x271.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-1024x924.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-768x693.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-1536x1386.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-500x451.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-440x397.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-261x235.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-311x281.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-363x327.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/001-1-270x244.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1636px) 100vw, 1636px\" /></p>\n<p>Making the plugin easy to set up is the first goal of the redesign process that our plugins go through. Thanks to common patterns used across all the plugins and options that clearly explain what they are for, even inexperienced users will be able to configure advanced auctions and set them up in every detail.    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 10px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142005\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1815\" height=\"1484\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1.jpg 1815w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-300x245.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-1024x837.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-768x628.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-1536x1256.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-500x409.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-440x360.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-261x213.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-311x254.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-363x297.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/002-1-270x221.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1815px) 100vw, 1815px\" /></p>\n<p>Most of the global options can be overridden from individual auctions: so, you can configure the general settings but change them on a product basis, if for example, you want that particular auction to charge a different fee amount.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>2- An integrated dashboard to monitor the auctions</h2>\n<p>    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 10px;\"></div>\n	<br />\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142042\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003-.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2000\" height=\"969\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003-.jpg 2000w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--300x145.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--1024x496.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--768x372.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--1536x744.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--500x242.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--440x213.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--261x126.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--311x151.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--363x176.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/003--270x131.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /></p>\n<p>We have implemented a dashboard where you can monitor in a very easy way the status of all the auctions: the current bid, the number of bids and bidders, the number of users watching the item, those who left their email address to be notified, and much more.<br />\nYou will be able to check everything at a glance without leaving the plugin panel.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>3- Create classic and/or reverse auctions</h2>\n<p>    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 10px;\"></div>\n	<br />\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142007\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1616\" height=\"1100\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1.jpg 1616w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-300x204.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-1024x697.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-768x523.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-1536x1046.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-500x340.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-440x300.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-261x178.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-311x212.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-363x247.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/004-1-270x184.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1616px) 100vw, 1616px\" /></p>\n<p>Since version 2.0 you will be able to create reverse auctions, that is auctions where its the lowest bid that wins, contrary to what happens with the standard auctions. This is a really sought-after feature, one of the most popular among our users. A typical example of how it is used is when you offer a job and you <strong>award it to the user who will carry it out at the lowest price</strong>.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>4- Start sealed auctions</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142008\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1091\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1.jpg 2000w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-300x164.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-1024x559.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-768x419.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-1536x838.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-500x273.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-440x240.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-261x142.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-311x170.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-363x198.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/005-1-270x147.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /></p>\n<p>Now it is possible to set an auction as sealed, meaning that bids are private and not visible to other users on the auction page. Bidders will only be able to see their own offers and receive a notification informing them if their bid is the highest one or if theres any higher bid, but they will not be able to see other users bids.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>5- Charge a fee to users who want to take part in an auction</h2>\n<p>    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 10px;\"></div>\n	<br />\nSince version 2.0, you can charge a fee to users who want to take part in an auction and bid. It is possible to either apply a global fee (the same amount to all auctions), disable the fee on some auctions or charge a different amount (smaller or higher) on selected auctions. When the user clicks on Pay now, they will be redirected to the checkout page to finalize the purchase.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142015\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1582\" height=\"1056\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee.jpg 1582w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-300x200.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-768x513.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-500x334.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-440x294.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-261x174.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-311x208.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-363x242.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fee-270x180.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1582px) 100vw, 1582px\" /></p>\n<p>We have also added another interesting feature, which is a confirmation reminder that the user has to click on before making a bid. In this way, you can remind bidders that they are committing to buy the item in case they win and reduce the number of accidental bids placed by those who did not think twice.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142012\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1389\" height=\"962\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid.jpg 1389w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid-300x208.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid-1024x709.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid-768x532.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid-500x346.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid-440x305.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid-261x181.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid-311x215.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid-363x251.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/confirmbid-270x187.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1389px) 100vw, 1389px\" /><br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>6- Verify the bidders payment method thanks to the integration with our Stripe plugin</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142013\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1864\" height=\"1083\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard.jpg 1864w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-300x174.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-1024x595.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-768x446.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-1536x892.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-500x291.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-440x256.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-261x152.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-311x181.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-363x211.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/creditcard-270x157.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1864px) 100vw, 1864px\" /></p>\n<p>It was not easy, but we managed to give a shape to one of the most popular features requested by our users. By combining YITH Auction for WooCommerce with <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-stripe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">YITH WooCommerce Stripe plugin</a>, you can also check whether users have a valid credit card saved in their account and prevent them from making a bid until one has been added.. On the auction page, users will see a notification that will redirect them to the Payment methods section in their account.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>7- More options for better management of automatic bids</h2>\n<p>    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 10px;\"></div>\n	<br />\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142016\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1811\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment.jpg 1811w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-300x177.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-1024x603.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-768x452.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-1536x905.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-500x295.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-440x259.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-400x235.jpg 400w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-769x452.jpg 769w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-261x154.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-311x183.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-363x214.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/increment-270x159.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1811px) 100vw, 1811px\" /></p>\n<p>It is possible to choose whether users can place manual or automatic bids: in the first case they will have to manually add a new bid whenever other users overbid them; when it comes with automatic bids, though, they can just enter the maximum amount they are willing to pay for that item and the system will automatically bid on their behalf to make sure their bid is always the best bid within the limit.</p>\n<p>Moreover, in this update, it is possible to set automatic bid amount increments both in an easy and advanced way. With the easy way, its the admin who sets a global bid increment, for example $10 and every automatic bid will be automatically incremented of that amount. With the advanced mode, it is possible to set automatic bid increments based on the current offer: for example, if the current offer is $100, the automatic bid will be +$20, but if the offer is $1000, the automatic bid will be +$100 and so on. <strong>This is a system used by the most popular auction platforms like eBay</strong>.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>8- More options for better management of unpaid items or auction rescheduling</h2>\n<p>    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 10px;\"></div>\n	<br />\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142009\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1958\" height=\"754\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1.jpg 1958w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-300x116.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-1024x394.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-768x296.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-1536x591.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-500x193.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-440x169.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-261x101.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-311x120.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-363x140.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/007-1-270x104.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1958px) 100vw, 1958px\" /></p>\n<p>Thanks to some advanced settings, now it is even easier to set up how to deal with an unpaid item or with auctions without a winner.</p>\n<p>For example, if the winner does not pay for the item within a certain time, you can choose whether to re-publish the auction, send an email to remind them of the payment or send an auction winner notification email to the second-highest bidder.</p>\n<p>If neither the second-highest bidder pays for the item, it is possible to set after how long the auction will be automatically published again.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>9- A Watchlist for all users who want to keep an eye on the auctions</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142017\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1872\" height=\"1378\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist.jpg 1872w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-300x221.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-1024x754.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-768x565.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-1536x1131.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-500x368.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-440x324.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-261x192.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-311x229.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-363x267.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/watchlist-270x199.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1872px) 100vw, 1872px\" /></p>\n<p>Before the update, the plugin could show a field on the auction page where users could type their email address and get notified about the auction progress.</p>\n<p>In version 2.0 we have added new functionality that we were able to find in many other online auction platforms: <strong>the watchlist</strong>. Thanks to it, users can save an auction product that they find interesting in a dedicated area in My account, and thanks to the integrated widget they can monitor and easily locate all the auctions they are watching. This feature helps enormously those users who are watching or bidding on many auctions at the same time, so they can see the status of all their auctions at a glance and in real-time, with current bids and time left for the auction to end.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>10- Compatibility with our Easy Login &amp; Register plugin to let users log in or register without leaving the auction page</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142044\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1627\" height=\"1052\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2.jpg 1627w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-300x194.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-1024x662.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-768x497.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-1536x993.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-500x323.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-440x284.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-261x169.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-311x201.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-363x235.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/easylogin2-270x175.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1627px) 100vw, 1627px\" /></p>\n<p>Users who want to place a bid will have to either register or log in and to do that they will have to leave the auction page. To prevent this from happening, we have added the integration with our plugin <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-easy-login-register-popup-for-woocommerce/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Easy Login &amp; Register Popup for WooCommerce</a>. If you install this plugin as well, your users will be able to register a new profile or log in to their account right from the auction page.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>11- A modern design and more customization options</h2>\n<p>    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 10px;\"></div>\n	<br />\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142010\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1950\" height=\"1362\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1.jpg 1950w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-300x210.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-1024x715.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-768x536.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-1536x1073.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-500x349.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-440x307.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-261x182.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-311x217.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-363x254.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/011-1-270x189.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1950px) 100vw, 1950px\" /></p>\n<p>And as we all know that you should also please the eye, we have accurately designed the new UI to make it modern and appealing. The user notifications use a graphic style inspired by the most famous online auction sites and it is possible to choose among 4 different countdown styles with customizable colors and make them suit any type of layout or theme.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1142011\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1765\" height=\"903\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1.jpg 1765w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-300x153.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-1024x524.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-768x393.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-1536x786.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-500x256.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-440x225.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-261x134.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-311x159.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-363x186.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/012-1-270x138.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1765px) 100vw, 1765px\" /></p>\n<p>Moreover, it is possible to customize the badges and change the countdown color when the auction is going to end soon (we suggest using red to emphasize the urgency!), add custom texts in the auction winner notifications, add the time zone code and many more options in the new <strong>version 2.0 of YITH Auction for WooCommerce!</strong></p>\n<p>Even if we might sound a bit pretentious, we feel like saying that we can now offer the best auction plugin for WooCommerce available in the market. Test it yourself and see if you can say its not true <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/12.0.0-1/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>To learn about all the new features of this new update, you can visit the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-auctions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">product page of YITH Auction for WooCommerce</a> or the <a href=\"https://plugins.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-auctions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">plugin live demo</a>. Dont forget to click on <strong>Launch Admin Demo</strong> button to see and test also the administration panel.</p>\n<p>As usual, we are always here for any questions you might have and we cant wait to read your feedback!</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:114:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/version-2-0-of-our-auction-plugin-for-woocommerce-will-make-your-jaw-drop/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"Create a recurring income stream using WooCommerce Subscriptions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/showcases/create-a-recurring-income-stream-using-woocommerce-subscriptions/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:109:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/showcases/create-a-recurring-income-stream-using-woocommerce-subscriptions/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 11 Aug 2020 12:23:58 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Showcases\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=1138445\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:374:\"Running a subscription business model is commonly known to boost your income. By charging a sometimes smaller amount but on a regular basis, in the longer term you create more revenue and a more stable income stream, often referred to as &#8220;recurring income&#8221;. Let&#8217;s run through different examples and combinations to create the perfect subscription [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"ronald2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14683:\"\n<p>Running a subscription business model is commonly known to boost your income. By charging a sometimes smaller amount but on a regular basis, in the longer term you create more revenue and a more stable income stream, often referred to as &#8220;recurring income&#8221;. Let&#8217;s run through different examples and combinations to create the perfect subscription product for your customer.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>If Amazon Prime can do it, you can do it too!</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Arguably the most<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-amazon-prime-service/\"> popular subscription is Amazon Prime, </a>but what do you actually subscribe to? It is a mix of services but mainly to get discounts, at least that is what most users believe. For so many things, you still need to pay extra like premium films or to download music, right? By offering free delivery and a constant reminder of your product-savings, you wouldn&#8217;t want to cheat yourself and shop elsewhere, even though you probably spend more. No doubt this will have you thinking, what it means to create a loyal customer base using subscriptions? There is much more psychology behind this marketing strategy and we encourage you to study this fascinating subject. <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00LFYXDNQ/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_hsch_vapi_tkin_p1_i1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored noreferrer\">Here is a book suggestion</a> that might help: &#8216;The Automatic Customer&#8217; by John Warrillow.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-1024x509.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1141534\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-1024x509.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-300x149.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-768x382.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-1536x764.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-500x249.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-440x219.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-261x130.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-311x155.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-363x181.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1-270x134.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/amazon_subs-1.jpg 1775w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you create a single subscription then any version of WooCommerce subscriptions would do. This is how it usually starts, but from customer&#8217;s experience, as soon as you begin to offer more complex subscription structures, starting dates, and free trials, you will realize that you will stumble upon many issues to which you need to compromise. But why would you need to compromise? After all, if you give your customers the feeling they are in control, they are more likely to commit.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, we have done our research too on what the customer wants, and together with your feedback we are confident we have managed to address every scenario and with <strong>YITH WooCommerce Subscription 2.0</strong> you can run your recurring business model exactly the way you planned it from the beginning. In a recent news announcement, we shared what is new and upcoming for YITH WooCommerce Subscriptions 2.0. But the power is often in the combination of two or more&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why would you need a subscription model in your business?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are so many types of businesses that could really make use of this recurring revenue model, so lets give you five examples with different ideas.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-1024x640.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1141535\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-1024x640.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-300x188.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-768x480.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-1536x960.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-500x313.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-440x275.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-261x163.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-311x194.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-363x227.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs-270x169.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/nespresso_subs.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1) Day to day consumables; </strong>like a coffee delivery service where each week you are sent freshly roasted coffee. And whether this is coffee, veg box, or even washing powder, you will make a customer for life and they will not need to worry about visiting the website and checking out every time. This model is probably the most common one where a store makes it easy for you to buy consumable products on a regular cycle.<br>The customer can take full control and give the subscription a holiday or order more or less depending on the variations you set up and the conditions you set for the customer to manage their subscription plan.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-1024x627.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1141539\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-1024x627.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-300x184.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-768x470.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-1536x940.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-500x306.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-440x269.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-261x160.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-311x190.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-363x222.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs-270x165.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/meatbox_subs.jpg 1977w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>But think outside the box and you can replace a consumable low-value item with a restaurant meal, craft project like a quilting project, free delivery, or even credits towards a bigger and more expensive purchase, like money off your next holiday with preferential dates.<br><strong><br>2) Products of high-value or part of a subscription plan;</strong> You could split payments for high-value items to make it more affordable for your customers to buy it now, rather than saving up. This is a proven model that is being used more and more, referred to as Buy Now Pay Later.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-1024x420.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1141536\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-1024x420.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-300x123.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-768x315.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-1536x630.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-500x205.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-440x181.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-261x107.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-311x128.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-363x149.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs-270x111.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/runfix_subs.jpg 1933w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3) Services and contract agreements;</strong> do you run a web agency and charge your customers for hosting, domain renewal, or even a maintenance service? Then youve also experienced late payments, many reminders, and possibly cash-flow issues. Setting up a subscription makes perfect sense to ensure your customer is making payments each month. And of course, if the client fails, you can set up your custom email reminders and allow them to catch up on a missed or failed payment from my account.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4) Set up a High-converting sales funnel.</strong> Do you want to convert more customers to use your services straight from your website? Adding the quick checkout for digital goods is a must, as this allows you to create a checkout form on any page and simply bypass the cart and payment pages. Set up a sales funnel with a clearly mapped out step and conversion path &#8211; no more need to add the subscription service to basket &gt; check out &gt; confirmation. It is all done from within the same page in this plugin combination.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1141537\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-300x169.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-768x432.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-500x281.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-440x248.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-261x147.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-311x175.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-363x204.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs-270x152.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/times_subs.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5) Memberships and online content;</strong> for online courses, downloads, and other restricted content to members only, YITH WooCommerce Subscriptions is the must-have tool to manage payments. <br>Many newspapers, magazines use this model, register to view 5 articles or only see the intro to get your attention, then pay a fee to see all the premium content. It is not very likely you will give life-time access for a single payment, but instead opt for the monthly plan in return for access to the exclusive content you have on your site. The <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-membership/\">YITH WooCommerce Membership</a> plugin is the perfect companion to create the ultimate membership plans with a weekly, monthly, or annual payment option. Just as we used in the example to set up an Amazon Prime service, you can add more functionality to expand this loyalty scheme.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>YITH WooCommerce Subscription Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Subscriptions managed by WooCommerce can give you a great boost in income, flexibility, and ultimately a choice to your customers. If you combine YITH WooCommerce Subscription with other plugins like a membership, multi-vendor, or checkout for digital goods, you can quickly create your ultimate business model.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-1024x500.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1141538\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-1024x500.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-300x147.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-768x375.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-1536x751.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-500x244.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-440x215.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-261x128.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-311x152.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-363x177.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs-270x132.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Alice_subs.jpg 1946w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Going back to the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-amazon-prime-service/\">Amazon Prime example</a> and how to create something similar. The model is probably as complex as it gets and for this, you need to combine plugins like Dynamic Pricing, and Membership. Also, Points and Rewards can help with giving credits in return for more benefits. But do you need this to start with, or can you pivot your business that creates loyalty, more customer spending, and increases your revenue just using the subscription plugin? The answer is probably, yes!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is difficult to not sound super enthusiastic about this type of business setup, but we&#8217;ve rarely seen a business adopting a subscription model to later abandon this. It is the most predictable type of revenue and if you ever plan to sell your business, you can confidently predict next year&#8217;s revenue and the size of your customer base. Now it has become an asset as well as a new revenue stream.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore all the options using the demo account and set up a sandbox site. From the plugins, you can enable any other YITH plugin to test the combined functionalities.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information and resources check out:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">YITH WooCommerce Subscriptions</a> &#8211; <a href=\"https://plugins.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\">Subscriptions Demo</a> (set up a sandbox site) &#8211; <a href=\"https://plugins.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Subscription Documentation</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:106:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/showcases/create-a-recurring-income-stream-using-woocommerce-subscriptions/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"Subscriptions 2.0: new features and improvements for this key plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:103:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/subscriptions-2-0-new-features-and-improvements-for-this-key-plugin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:111:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/subscriptions-2-0-new-features-and-improvements-for-this-key-plugin/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 10 Aug 2020 13:19:38 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"YITH News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=1139988\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:340:\"We are ecstatic to announce our newly upgraded subscription plugin YITH WooCommerce Subscriptions 2.0. This is one of the flagship projects we have been waiting for to present to you for some time. Not only does it give you a more reliable experience and results, but the functionality and design is also something that sets [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"ronald2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9906:\"<p>We are ecstatic to announce our newly upgraded subscription plugin YITH WooCommerce Subscriptions 2.0.</p>\n<p>This is one of the flagship projects we have been waiting for to present to you for some time. Not only does it give you a more reliable experience and results, but the functionality and design is also something that sets new standards for any WordPress plugin.</p>\n<p>We focused on integration and compatibility with some of the best selling YITH plugins but just as important is the <strong>Gutenberg Blocks</strong> and <strong>Elementor widgets.</strong> There are so many new features that will make your life much easier and no more need to hire a developer to make it work for you.</p>\n<p>So lets give you a tour of whats new with YITH WooCommmerce Subscriptions.</p>\n<h3>5 of the most exciting new features (yes, there are many more)</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Improved UX</strong> for better subscription set up and management for the store owner.</li>\n<li><strong>More flexibility for the user:</strong> you can give more options to customers and allow them to pause, renew and make payments from my account</li>\n<li><strong>Gutenberg Block and Elementor integration</strong> to create a beautiful layout with your pricing subscription plans</li>\n<li>We are making use of the <strong>latest cronjob with WooCommerce integration</strong>, making renewal payments more reliable to being charged</li>\n<li><strong>Subscription dashboard</strong> to see all your active, renewal, failed and canceled subscriptions with custom colored labels.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1141297\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1164\" height=\"649\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-300x167.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-1024x571.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-768x428.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-1536x856.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-2048x1142.jpg 2048w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-500x279.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-440x245.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-261x145.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-311x173.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-363x202.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub1-270x150.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1164px) 100vw, 1164px\" /></p>\n<h3>And here are 5 further improvements to subscriptions.</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>An improvement in the <strong>use of variations to create different subscription plans</strong> and allow the customer to up-, or downgrade</li>\n<li>Better <strong>emailing and automated correspondence options;</strong> set your message and email content and never worry again on reminding customers.</li>\n<li><strong>Custom call to action labels;</strong> change the label text of the buttons to subscribe, free trial, or the fee information.</li>\n<li><strong>More options for my-account</strong> to allow the customer to renew subscriptions</li>\n<li><strong>GDPR rules improvements</strong> with the auto-deletion of users after a set cancellation period.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>And there is much more to discover</p>\n<p><img class=\"wp-image-1141305 aligncenter\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"748\" height=\"610\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2.jpg 1372w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2-300x244.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2-1024x834.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2-768x626.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2-500x407.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2-440x359.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2-261x213.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2-311x253.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2-363x296.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/sub2-270x220.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 748px) 100vw, 748px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Functionality and technical upgrade of the subscription plugin</h2>\n<p>The Subscription plugin has been developed by Emanuela, who is one of the most experienced crew members. She developed the first version, and by giving plugin support and hearing of our customers wishes as well as new technology and the help of Sara Presenti, our UX/UI designer, she created this new version of one of the most popular plugins. It was not always that simple and also this journey threw a few challenges like the Gutenberg integration to really create a fully customizable block with options to change the order, colors, buttons, and more layout settings. Furthermore, it is most important that when users upgrade to the new plugin, this process is effortless and seamless, so this required some rigorous testing.</p>\n<p><div class=\"yithemes-interview\">\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-lg-2 col-sm-2 col-xs-3 profile-name\">\n			                <img src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/emanuela-castorina.jpg\" alt=\"Emanuela - Developer\" class=\"interview-picture\" loading=\"lazy\">\n			            <p class=\"interview-name\">Emanuela - Developer</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"col-lg-10 col-sm-10 col-xs-9\">\n            <div class=\"interview-content\">\n				 &#8220;The new version of YITH WooCommerce Subscriptions will automatically migrate your currently active subscriptions to be handled by a new and more reliable cronjob system to trigger the renewal payments. We have more updates in the planning but you can always reach out with your requests.&#8221;             </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: inherit;font-family: inherit;font-size: 30px\">Designing the subscriptions plugin to make life easy, really easy</span></p>\n<p>All of our updated plugins are being redesigned by Sara Presenti, who is the UX/UI designer of YITH. When redesigning a plugin from the bottom up, you can use this opportunity to question every aspect and feature that is useful for the store owner as well as the customer. Being able to navigate, understand, and change each different feature and setting, and of course, the functionality that you would want to experience as a customer. It really can be very complex, but thankfully through research and many designs, we are confident you are able to make all the changes without involving a developer to further customize this plugin.</p>\n<p><div class=\"yithemes-interview\">\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-lg-2 col-sm-2 col-xs-3 profile-name\">\n			                <img src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/sara-presenti.jpg\" alt=\"Sara - UX designer\" class=\"interview-picture\" loading=\"lazy\">\n			            <p class=\"interview-name\">Sara - UX designer</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"col-lg-10 col-sm-10 col-xs-9\">\n            <div class=\"interview-content\">\n				 &#8220;Customers like to feel they get a good deal. Comparing different options and subscriptions side by side in an attractive way that will give your customers control and the sense they choose the best deal from them, which will lead to more conversions.&#8221;             </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div></p>\n<p>Adding to this, you can now create highly converting landing pages yourself very easily. We have integrated Gutenberg Blocks and the ever so popular Elementor page builder. Every part from the boxes, buttons to the content you can style easily yourself now. All you need now are the page visitors to click through to the checkout.</p>\n<p><img class=\"wp-image-1141299 aligncenter\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1011\" height=\"924\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3.png 1474w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-300x274.png 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-1024x935.png 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-768x701.png 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-500x457.png 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-440x402.png 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-261x238.png 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-311x284.png 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-363x331.png 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-270x247.png 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1011px) 100vw, 1011px\" /></p>\n<h2>What is next for YITH Subscriptions for WooCommerce?</h2>\n<p>This plugin update is only the beginning of many improvements in the planning. We are already testing it with new integrations like PayPal (for more payment methods, in fact, over 200 different types). We are hoping to integrate more YITH plugins to extend the functionality as we did with Points and Rewards and YITH Membership for WooCommerce.<br />\nAlso, think about subscription creations from the admin panel, improved dashboards, and email notifications.</p>\n<p>Like all YITH plugins, you can test <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">YITH WooCommerce Subscriptions</a> on our <a href=\"https://plugins.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\">Subscriptions Demo Site</a> (and set up a sandbox site) read more on the <a href=\"https://plugins.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-subscription/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Subscription Documentation.</a> Plus, you can leave a comment, reach out to the support or chat.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:108:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/subscriptions-2-0-new-features-and-improvements-for-this-key-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"Crew member Highlight; Carlos the Auction plugin developer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/crew-member-highlight-carlos-the-auction-plugin-developer/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/crew-member-highlight-carlos-the-auction-plugin-developer/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 31 Jul 2020 12:14:18 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"YITH News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=1139824\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:339:\"It is a really great thing to introduce our crew members to the wider YITH audience and users. Many of the developers and support staff work hard &#8216;behind the scenes&#8217;. Especially now we don&#8217;t attend any physical WordCamps where our customers get to meet some of the crew. So let&#8217;s find out about Carlos and [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"ronald2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7280:\"<p>It is a really great thing to introduce our crew members to the wider YITH audience and users. Many of the developers and support staff work hard &#8216;behind the scenes&#8217;. Especially now we don&#8217;t attend any physical WordCamps where our customers get to meet some of the crew.<br />\nSo let&#8217;s find out about Carlos and what he has been up to in the last few weeks. (the title is a big hint here)</p>\n<p>Carlos has been working at YITH since coming out of University, actually whilst doing his studies he found himself as a scholar learning his practical skills with us. Asking how to describe working at YITH, Carlos answered:</p>\n<blockquote><p>&#8220;Great, day by day since 2016 I improve my skills as a developer and it&#8217;s really comforting that my work is helping a lot of customers in their shop. I studied computer engineering at the University of La Laguna. And after finishing, I was presented with the opportunity to work at YITH thanks to the scholarship&#8221;</p></blockquote>\n<p>How would you describe a typical day?</p>\n<blockquote><p>&#8220;I start work at 8 oclock. I spend 15 minutes checking task that my colleagues send me. After that, I start to work on tickets and I try to help customers to fix their problems on their shop pages. After lunch, I work on a different project. Plugins update, bug fixing, and improvement. Always, you can find something to do. Each day is a different day <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/12.0.0-1/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p></blockquote>\n<p>Do you have a particular project that you manage?</p>\n<blockquote><p>&#8220;Yes, I have been very busy updating <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-auctions/\">YITH Auctions for WooCommerce </a>in the last few months, with a big new upgraded release out soon&#8221;</p></blockquote>\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemHeader\">\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemTitleDescContainer\">\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemTitleContainer\">\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemTitle exportItemTitle freebirdCustomFont\" role=\"heading\" aria-describedby=\"i.desc.1164400879\">What were the struggles you experienced working on this plugin?</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemTitle exportItemTitle freebirdCustomFont\" role=\"heading\" aria-describedby=\"i.desc.1164400879\">&#8220;The ignorance of how an auction page works, but after an in-depth study. This plugin is helping many people in their shop.&#8221;</div>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsTextTextItemContainer\">\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemHeader\">\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemTitleDescContainer\">\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemTitleContainer\">\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemTitle exportItemTitle freebirdCustomFont\" role=\"heading\" aria-describedby=\"i.desc.569691543\">Do you have a favorite type of customer? And what makes them unique?</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsItemItemTitle exportItemTitle freebirdCustomFont\" role=\"heading\" aria-describedby=\"i.desc.569691543\">&#8220;I think the best customer is the one that makes our job easier to try to solve their problems with the support as soon as possible.&#8221;</div>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><figure id=\"attachment_1112989\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1112989\" style=\"width: 1000px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img class=\"wp-image-1112989 size-full\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Copy-of-YITH-header-4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Copy-of-YITH-header-4.png 1000w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Copy-of-YITH-header-4-300x84.png 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Copy-of-YITH-header-4-768x215.png 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Copy-of-YITH-header-4-261x73.png 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Copy-of-YITH-header-4-311x87.png 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Copy-of-YITH-header-4-363x102.png 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Copy-of-YITH-header-4-270x76.png 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1112989\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Carlos in the center doing a talk at WordCamp Chiclana in 2020, with Sara (left) and Nando our CEO (right)</figcaption></figure></p>\n<p>Carlos is one of our crew members that regularly attend, and also speaks at, mainly Spanish WordCamps.</p>\n<p>As a speaker during WordCamp Chiclana, Carlos shared how to correctly extend the WordPress functionalities, not to cause conflicts with the rest of the web components and keep them in the future, since an incorrect implementation can bring us many problems. <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/events/wordcamp-chiclana-did-we-forget-to-mention-the-food/\">Read about it here &gt;</a></p>\n<p>Carlos was born and bred in Santa Cruz de Tenerife and in his words, it is a special place mainly due to the good weather all year round.</p>\n<blockquote><p>&#8220;I love the beach. Whenever I can I go swimming and enjoy the waves and the tranquility.&#8221;</p></blockquote>\n<p>What food or drink gets you motivated?</p>\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsTextItemWrapper freebirdFormviewerViewItemsTextTextItemContainer\">\n<blockquote>\n<div class=\"freebirdFormviewerViewItemsTextShortText freebirdFormviewerViewItemsTextDisabledText freebirdThemedInput\" aria-describedby=\"c731\">\n<p>&#8220;When I start the day, after a coffee, my head starts working quickly. But for food you can&#8217;t beat agood pasta or a typical Canarian dish &#8220;Papas, pias y costillas&#8221;</p>\n</div>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/category/yit-news/\">Check out</a> other crew-members stories and how they started working at YITH. If you want to connect with Carlos you can do so via twitter <a href=\"https://twitter.com/crodriguezbrito\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">@crodriguezbrito</a></p>\n<p><figure id=\"attachment_1112924\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1112924\" style=\"width: 1000px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"wp-image-1112924 size-full\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"453\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020.jpg 1000w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-300x136.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-768x348.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-261x118.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-311x141.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-363x164.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-270x122.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1112924\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Carlos is sitting down on the front row, first from the right.</figcaption></figure></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/crew-member-highlight-carlos-the-auction-plugin-developer/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"Reduce your checkout abandonment rate with our new version of Multi-step Checkout\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:117:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/reduce-your-checkout-abandonment-rate-with-our-new-version-of-multi-step-checkout/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:126:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/reduce-your-checkout-abandonment-rate-with-our-new-version-of-multi-step-checkout/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 01 Jul 2020 15:17:06 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"YITH News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=1133254\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:320:\"Everyone running an e-commerce shop is suffering the plague of an increasing rate of users abandoned carts and checkouts. In the past decades the abandoned cart rate has been growing to reach stable values between 50 and 70%. This means that more than half of those users that add a product to the cart will [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Sara Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9346:\"<p>Everyone running an e-commerce shop is suffering the plague of an <strong>increasing rate of users abandoned carts and checkouts</strong>.<br />\nIn the past decades the abandoned cart rate has been growing to reach stable values between 50 and 70%.</p>\n<p>This means that <strong>more than half of those users that add a product to the cart will not finalize the purchase</strong>. Its such a considerable rate that it cannot be ignored and that should push every online business to an accurate and in-depth analysis of what is causing it and what solutions are available.</p>\n<p>Why do users abandon shopping carts?</p>\n<p>There might be many reasons why users abandon a shopping cart or leave the checkout process and they can differ based on the products that you sell, on your target and on the devices used by your site visitors.</p>\n<p>In general, most users state that they leave because:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>They see additional fees showing up in the checkout, like too high shipping rates or tax that they had not taken into account;</li>\n<li>They are asked to create an account and fill out a huge number of fields (first and last name, address, phone number and so on) which took too long;</li>\n<li>They find the checkout process too complicated: too many details to add and unclear descriptions made them feel so frustrated that they prefer putting the purchase off.</li>\n<li>Mobile user experience is not the same as a desktop. Long forms with irrelevant fields stop mobile users from checking out.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A well-built checkout, then, is essential to help users finalize the purchase with a serene attitude. Our Multi-Step Checkout plugin allows <strong>splitting the checkout process into smaller steps</strong>, guiding users one step after the other until they complete the order without overwhelming them with too many details to add on one page.</p>\n<p>To be able to offer an even better user experience, we have just released an updated version to refresh the plugin interface and make it even more usable and above all to add the most popular options in demand.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 50px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h2>Multistep checkout &#8211; whats new</h2>\n<p>    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 15px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h3>1- The new user interface</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1133256\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1710\" height=\"886\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01.jpg 1710w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-300x155.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-1024x531.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-768x398.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-1536x796.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-500x259.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-440x228.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-261x135.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-311x161.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-363x188.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/01-270x140.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1710px) 100vw, 1710px\" /></a></p>\n<p>As well as for all the plugins that we have redesigned during the past year, it was time for Multi-Step Checkout of a new panel redesign. We carried out a UX analysis and repositioned the options to make them more intuitive and the plugin easier to set up.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 15px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h3>2- A new style for the checkout steps, modern and even more mobile-friendly</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1133257\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1508\" height=\"775\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02.jpg 1508w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02-300x154.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02-1024x526.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02-768x395.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02-500x257.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02-440x226.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02-261x134.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02-311x160.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02-363x187.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/02-270x139.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1508px) 100vw, 1508px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The plugin already offers many styles for the checkout steps so that every user can choose the one that best suits the theme. In this update, however, we have added one more style, based on a modern graphic design that fits any kind of e-commerce shop. A minimal design and SVG icons grant a perfect output on every device, also retina ones. This new style works great also on mobile devices, where the steps will work as accordion menus, as recommended by usability best practice.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 15px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h3>3- More step customization options</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1133258\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1873\" height=\"991\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03.jpg 1873w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-300x159.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-1024x542.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-768x406.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-1536x813.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-500x265.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-440x233.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-261x138.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-311x165.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-363x192.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/03-270x143.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1873px) 100vw, 1873px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Now for every step, you can customize colors (current, previous and next step) and choose one of the high-quality icons we designed or, as an alternative, upload your custom one. We decided to increase the number of options so that with just a few clicks you can create an original-design checkout totally in line with your e-commerce look.<br />\n    <div class=\"spacer\" style=\"height: 15px;\"></div>\n	</p>\n<h3>4- Option to merge Billing/Shipping and Order Info/Payment steps.</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1133259\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1873\" height=\"675\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04.jpg 1873w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-300x108.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-1024x369.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-768x277.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-1536x554.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-500x180.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-440x159.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-261x94.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-311x112.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-363x131.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/04-270x97.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1873px) 100vw, 1873px\" /></a></p>\n<p>According to many usability studies, a multi-step checkout is really effective when the total steps are no more than four because too many steps would slow down the purchase process, not to mention making it a frustrating task. Thats why we have listened to your requests and added an option to merge the two Billing and Shipping tabs into one step (the Shipping tab can however be disabled if theres no product to be shipped) as well as Order Info and Payment. This way you will be able to build a checkout with only 3 steps: easier and quicker than this would be impossible.</p>\n<p>Huge thanks to the many users of our YITH Multi-step Checkout that with their precious feedback helped us improve the plugin and make it one of the best ones on the market. We cant wait to hear what you think about it!</p>\n<p>Take a look at the <a href=\"https://plugins.yithemes.com/yith-woocommerce-multi-step-checkout/\">new demo of YITH WooCommerce Multi-step Checkout &gt;</a></p>\n<p>Visit the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-multi-step-checkout/\">landing page of the plugin YITH WooCommerce Multi-step Checkout &gt;</a></p>\n<p>Note: for a better user experience and to keep the checkout abandonment rate even lower, we suggest you combine YITH Multi-step checkout plugin with our <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-easy-login-register-for-woocommerce/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>YITH Easy Login &amp; Register for WooCommerce</strong></a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:122:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/reduce-your-checkout-abandonment-rate-with-our-new-version-of-multi-step-checkout/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"Meet Andrea Grillo; a developer with a Sicilian zest for life.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/meet-andrea-grillo-a-developer-with-a-sicilian-zest-for-life/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/meet-andrea-grillo-a-developer-with-a-sicilian-zest-for-life/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 22 Jun 2020 14:30:04 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"YITH News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=1134117\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:340:\"There are few people like Andrea, luckily at YITH, we have many with similar characteristics maybe because Andrea is a big influence or he fits right in the YITH family. Andrea just loves life and the little things that are available to enjoy this. From motorbikes, fishing, enjoying a coffee with colleagues to general helping [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"ronald2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7521:\"<p>There are few people like Andrea, luckily at YITH, we have many with similar characteristics maybe because Andrea is a big influence or he fits right in the YITH family. Andrea just loves life and the little things that are available to enjoy this. From motorbikes, fishing, enjoying a coffee with colleagues to general helping customers and colleagues alike, Andrea is there. He studied computer science at the University of Catania and graduated in 2011. He grew up in Acireale on the Italian island of Sicily with his brother and parents.</p>\n<blockquote><p>Here we have all you want: the sea and mountains, people are kind (almost always haha) and enjoy a good climate, even during the winter. There are wonderful places to see, if you&#8217;ve never been here you have to take a trip around here, maybe by motorbike Sicily is the place I call home, having also lived in Catanzaro (Calabria) and for a couple of months in Milan (Lombardia).</p></blockquote>\n<p>Andrea started working at YITH in 2013 making him one of the longest-serving developers in the company. Before this, it was not a straightforward start to becoming a developer</p>\n<blockquote><p>In 2012, after I did several work-experiences coming out of university, I shortly worked in Calabria for a startup which I really enjoyed. Unfortunately, it all ended in January 2013. In the meantime, I accepted position as a substitute at school for a computer-science teacher at the Hotel Institute of Catania. Luckily, my cousin introduced me to Nando, the CEO of YITH. He had just finished the offices in Aci Saint Antonio and was looking for collaborators. After a brief interview, Nando asked me to join the company and I felt right at home from the beginning. This was in 2013 and as you see, this adventure continues today :-)</p></blockquote>\n<p><figure id=\"attachment_1134127\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1134127\" style=\"width: 699px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"wp-image-1134127\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Andrea_milano2018-scaled-e1592834720768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"699\" height=\"523\" /><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1134127\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Andrea taking a selfie during WordCamp Milan&#8217;s contributor day in 2018. Traveling to WordCamps is a great way to meet many customers and for them to connect with the team.</figcaption></figure></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In general, the team likes to stick to set times working together. It gives a sense of teamwork and joined achievement. Also, Andrea can be found working in the Sicilian office on most days. What does a typical workday look like?</p>\n<blockquote><p>I start work at 9 &#8216;o&#8217;clock. Before that, I spend 15 minutes checking emails and other little tasks that my colleagues send me. After that, I manage the support requests for the rest of the morning. After lunch, I work on a different project. Plugins update, bug fixing, and improvement, new plugins or projects, ideas that arise during our weekly meetings &#8230; there is no shortage of work, you can always find something to do!</p></blockquote>\n<p>What else is important in your job you do today?</p>\n<blockquote><p>I like writing code so I like my job but at YITH it is different. I have full control of the project I&#8217;m working on, I can study it, find the solution, and implement it according to what I think is the best solution/technology at the moment!</p>\n<p>Also, the coffee and lunch breaks! It&#8217;s an important moment in the working day. During this moment you can talk with colleagues and share about life or about something that is not linked to our jobs&#8230; it&#8217;s a good moment! Unfortunately, the Covid-19 emergency has stolen this from us, though we are confident, we will have these moments again soon!</p></blockquote>\n<p>Customer support is a big part of most developers daily tasks. This gets the highest priority and getting appreciated is something that most developers find very important. No surprise that Andrea takes great care in making sure the customer is valued and a solution is found quickly and when this gratitude is returned if feels great.</p>\n<blockquote><p>We try to be professional but friendly with customers, this is what makes our job special. A great show of gratitude is when a customer opens a support request simply to say &#8220;Merry Christmas&#8221; or to communicate an achieved success or to know if we are safe during this bad period. I think this is truly special.<br />\nIn general, we try to create a family atmosphere, both with colleagues but in particular with customers. With colleagues, the relationship is realy very good! With many of them, we also socialize outside of work.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Andrea is the main author of <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-multi-vendor/\">YITH WooCommerce Multi-Vendor</a> or the marketplace plugin for WooCommerce. But this is just one of a big list of projects that Andrea has been involved with. For him, the biggest challenge is to plan for unknown future improvements.</p>\n<blockquote><p>You must always analyze and plan everything before starting to write code. Think about how the software could evolve in the future because it is impossible to think of adding everything immediately, but you know customers will come up with some amazing and useful features. A plugin is something that will grow and evolve over time.</p></blockquote>\n<p>One of the regular questions of what food that gets Andrea motivated the most is anything cooked on the grill but suggest a pineapple on pizza and he will tell you its a crime&#8230; we should have known this when asking an Italian. Back to what Andrea loves the most</p>\n<blockquote><p>Motorbike! I like to ride a motorbike! I love to travel and discover new places by motorbike, in my opinion, it is something wonderful. I also like fishing, hiking in the mountains, going to the sea. I really love DIY and gardening too! Pretty much everything that involves spending time outdoors, and even better the Sicilian outdoors! </p></blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/category/yit-news/\">Check out</a> other crew-members stories and how they started working at YITH. If you want to connect with Andrea you can do so via twitter <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GrilloAndrea\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">@GrilloAndrea</a></p>\n<p><figure id=\"attachment_1112924\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1112924\" style=\"width: 1000px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"wp-image-1112924 size-full\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"453\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020.jpg 1000w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-300x136.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-768x348.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-261x118.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-311x141.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-363x164.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/team-yith-2020-270x122.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1112924\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Andrea; sitting down, third from the left</figcaption></figure></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/meet-andrea-grillo-a-developer-with-a-sicilian-zest-for-life/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"How to use WooCommerce as a catalog only; 5 use cases\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/free-plugins/woocommerce-extension-catalog-mode/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/free-plugins/woocommerce-extension-catalog-mode/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 09 Jun 2020 16:14:42 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Free Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=761327\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:327:\"What is Catalog Mode for an e-commerce store? When started using WooCommerce and have added products showing on the front-end but you do not allow visitors to purchase them, you can disable the native WooCommerce cart and checkout in a simple click. Also if you prefer, you can hide the prices from being displayed to [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Ronald Gijsel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11718:\"<h3>What is Catalog Mode for an e-commerce store?</h3>\n<p>When started using WooCommerce and have added products showing on the front-end but you do not allow visitors to purchase them, you can disable the native WooCommerce cart and checkout in a simple click. Also if you prefer, you can hide the prices from being displayed to visitors. Depending on the plugin and if this is a free or the premium version, you can adjust many more settings. Some people also refer to this type of solution as an e-commerce brochure site, if it is a more permanent solution. Lets dive a little deeper into different problems it can solve.</p>\n<p>So lets start with 5 very good user scenarios whereby you would want to use a catalog mode plugin for WooCommerce.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The store is populated but not ready to sell. Starting and populating a new shop and you are waiting to finalize pricing and the payment methods? By having the product pages live, it can help with getting the sitemap indexed by Google or share them on social media to create interest</li>\n<li>A temporary online store closure; holidays or due to unforeseen circumstances like the corona outbreak. You can simply display a message with more details instead of the add to cart button.</li>\n<li>External link but with a custom CTA; like a rental site with an external booking platform</li>\n<li>Only logged in customers can make a purchase, though every visitor can see the products. Also referred to as a trade or wholesale site that requires some kind of application to allow customers to see the pricing and checkout.</li>\n<li>Your products are custom made or are no longer for sale; for example, when artisan crafters have created custom pieces of furniture or jewelry and showcase these to inspire the next customer to get in touch.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>These are just 5 examples and weve seen many more use cases, making this the must-have plugin to have for every WooCommerce site, whether this is enabled or disabled to use when you need it.</p>\n<p><img class=\"wp-image-1117558 aligncenter\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"701\" height=\"539\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005.jpg 815w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005-300x231.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005-768x591.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005-500x385.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005-440x339.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005-261x201.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005-311x239.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005-363x279.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-005-270x208.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px\" /></p>\n<h3>What are the key features of the Free version of YITH WooCommerce Catalog Mode?</h3>\n<p>The most important feature you can do out of the box which is to turn your WooCommerce store into a brochure. This covers the first two user-cases and disables your cart and checkout pages.</p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-1117555 aligncenter\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"699\" height=\"405\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002.jpg 1678w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-300x174.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-1024x594.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-768x445.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-1536x891.jpg 1536w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-500x290.jpg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-440x255.jpg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-261x151.jpg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-311x180.jpg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-363x210.jpg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/catalog-mode-002-270x157.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></p>\n<p>For many store owners, this is what you need it most for, to stop online orders. But remain visible with all products, categories and archive pages, there to be seen. Seen by actual visitors but also bots (Google Indexing) and linking from referral sites.<br />\nJust out of the box, WooCommerce has a great structure to manage taxonomies (categories and tags) there are many scenarios whereby you only need to install WooCommerce and the YITH WooCommerce Catalog Mode plugin, to manage a whole new type of online stores, service providers and galleries. Think of art, custom products, inspirational fashion images, party providers, and more unique products and services that most people will not buy with an online checkout without making some serious inquiries.</p>\n<div class=\"center-block\"><a class=\"download-link\" title=\"Download File\" href=\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-catalog-mode.zip\">Download for free</a></div>\n<p>Both the free and the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-catalog-mode/\">premium version</a> allows you to hide the add to cart button or replace this with a different text. It could link to a contact or booking form for example. Asking yourself what you want to achieve, not all solutions need a plugin.</p>\n<h3>Create a WooCommerce brochure without a plugin</h3>\n<p>It gets better as you can hide the add to cart button with a simple line of code. Add the following code to the functions.php<br />\nAs always when adding custom code, take a backup, use an FTP client like Filezilla and test it!</p>\n<pre>add_action( \'init\', \'hide_add_to_cart\', 30 );\r\nfunction hide_add_to_cart() {\r\n\r\n//Remove from single product page\r\n\r\nremove_action( \'woocommerce_single_product_summary\', \'woocommerce_template_single_add_to_cart\', 30 );\r\n\r\n//Remove from Shop/Categories pages\r\n\r\nadd_filter( \'woocommerce_loop_add_to_cart_link\', \'__return_empty_string\', 99 );\r\n\r\n}</pre>\n<h3>Added functionality that comes with the premium features</h3>\n<p>Most likely you will get used to the flexibility of the different functions the free plugin offers and want something more. For example, what if you need to set separate rules that do not apply all visitors or products? Then it makes so much more sense to use the premium version.</p>\n<p><img class=\"wp-image-1133816 aligncenter\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"699\" height=\"414\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode.png 1200w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-300x178.png 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1024x607.png 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-768x455.png 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-500x296.png 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-440x261.png 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-261x155.png 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-311x184.png 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-363x215.png 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-270x160.png 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /><br />\nYou can set rules that set the catalog mode for a specific category or tag only. A great usage example would be that if you are planning to sell remnants on a specific day, but want to list the products so people can browse. In this way, you can create a huge demand for the items and give everyone a fair chance to buy them on the day. All you need to do is to remove the rule youve set up and everything is available to be purchased.</p>\n<p><img class=\"wp-image-1133813 aligncenter\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/f904c274b35290381a3ddbbc358318db.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"699\" height=\"411\" /></p>\n<p>By enabling it for guest users, you can use any contact form to create an application form to recruit trade buyers to shop from you. A super simple way to create a wholesale or trade buying website.</p>\n<p>Other options including selecting catalog mode for certain categories, tags, and products, but also the location and of course the logged out users only.<br />\n<img class=\" wp-image-1133815 aligncenter\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"455\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1.png 1141w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1-300x195.png 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1-1024x667.png 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1-768x500.png 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1-500x326.png 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1-440x287.png 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1-261x170.png 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1-311x203.png 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1-363x236.png 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/YITH_WooCommerce_Catalog_Mode-1-270x176.png 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></p>\n<p>Creating an inquiry form is super easy now and even better when you connect it with your favorite form builder. Just imagine the possibilities when you add conditional fields, image uploads, and more the options are limitless to make a brochure site into a landing page and lead-capture, whilst using the WooCommerce structure and layout.<br />\nThe plugin has been integrated with Contact Form 7, Gravity Forms, Formidable Forms, and Ninja Forms. So adding a form to each of the products you can send the specific inquiry straight to you or even a third party, depending on the rules you set up. This can work for sites that show custom-made of hand-made products and the artist or professional would need to discuss more details. But also this could work for a house rental site and the visitor can get in touch with the home-owner directly.</p>\n<p>The options with the Catalog Mode for WooCommerce are endless and it should really be a base-plugin for so many types of businesses and something you can just enable when you need it.</p>\n<p>Like all YITH plugins, YITH WooCommerce Catalog Mode works with all plugins and in particular the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-request-a-quote/\">Request a Quote for WooCommerce</a>, <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-multi-vendor/\">Multi-Vendor</a> and <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-product-bundles/\">Product Bundles.</a></p>\n<div class=\"center-block\"><a class=\"download-link\" title=\"Check out Catalog Mode\" href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-catalog-mode/\">Get Catalog Mode Premium</a></div>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/free-plugins/woocommerce-extension-catalog-mode/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"17\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"WordCamp Europe 2020  a very smooth virtual experience\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/wordcamp-europe-2020-a-very-smooth-virtual-experience/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:97:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/wordcamp-europe-2020-a-very-smooth-virtual-experience/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 09 Jun 2020 16:08:09 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"YITH News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=1132049\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:327:\"If you&#8217;d asked me to create a virtual conference for almost 9000 attendees from 140 countries, 30 sponsors, 2 main tracks a ton of zoom rooms for sponsors and more, I&#8217;d probably run away and hide&#8230; Admittedly this was achieved by a group of volunteers and not by a single person, however, we feel the [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"ronald2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9746:\"<p>If you&#8217;d asked me to create a virtual conference for almost 9000 attendees from 140 countries, 30 sponsors, 2 main tracks a ton of zoom rooms for sponsors and more, I&#8217;d probably run away and hide&#8230; Admittedly this was achieved by a group of volunteers and not by a single person, however, we feel the result of achievement should be highlighted right at the start.<br />\nFrom 4-6 June 2020, we should all have gathered in Porto for another edition of the increasingly successful WordCamp Europe. Instead, due to the outbreak, we were able to join in virtually. The team had plenty of notice to make this happen, but still, planning is one thing and to pull it off is another thing.</p>\n<p><img class=\"wp-image-1132055 aligncenter\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"801\" height=\"450\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q.jpeg 1366w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q-300x169.jpeg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q-500x281.jpeg 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q-440x247.jpeg 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q-261x147.jpeg 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q-311x175.jpeg 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q-363x204.jpeg 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/EZ3kblSWsAcX53Q-270x152.jpeg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 801px) 100vw, 801px\" /></p>\n<h2>What is WordCamp Europe?</h2>\n<p>A WordCamp is an event where loads of WordPress users, companies, speakers, and everything in-between, come together for a few days and share knowledge. Often this is combined with a contributor day on which WordPress users can help to make WordPress as an opensource platform better. Contributions can be made to the code, translations, support, documentation, and community to name just a few areas.<br />\nThese types of events can be held in any city, country or also on a continent. In Europe, it is a tradition for this to be held once a year in a different city and country. Last year, WordCamp Europe was held in Berlin for example.</p>\n<h2>Why does YITH sponsors WordCamps?</h2>\n<p>Sponsoring a WordCamp is more than just adding your logo and brand to a prominent place or to sell more. Actually, we see very little immediate results from sponsoring WordCamps. But we have learned over the years that this is not the type of event to set any expectations other than sharing knowledge, joy, and making lots of friends. Yes, we take part and sponsor to make WordPress a nicer and more inclusive community. Obviously, we do share some information about our company and are there to answer any questions. We firmly believe in building up a relationship with users and the wider community and somehow this always comes back and reflects in a happy and stable customer base.</p>\n<h2>We did not share swag but knowledge instead.</h2>\n<p>If you&#8217;ve been to a WordCamp before and bumped into our sponsor stand, you&#8217;ve probably received an iconic YITH swag t-shirt. A bit more difficult in a virtual world, although a virtual t-shirt does not fade or shrink in the wash, so we opted for a session with a presentation. As our community and partnership manager, I had the honor to share some company history, a presentation on &#8217;10 ways to identify opportunities for every WooCommerce store&#8217;, and followed by a Q&amp;A.<br />\nThe sponsor&#8217;s area had three main zoom rooms that could be accessed by the attendees. Each sponsor had an allocated time to use as a platform to do all sorts of activities, including quizzes, demonstrations, AMA sessions, presentations, and more.</p>\n<p><figure id=\"attachment_1132074\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1132074\" style=\"width: 799px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"wp-image-1132074 \" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"799\" height=\"450\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310.png 1293w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310-300x169.png 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310-1024x577.png 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310-768x432.png 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310-500x282.png 500w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310-440x248.png 440w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310-261x147.png 261w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310-311x175.png 311w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310-363x204.png 363w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/unknown-4-e1591712381310-270x152.png 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 799px) 100vw, 799px\" /><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1132074\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Presentation by Ronald on how to identify 10 opportunities for every WooCommerce store.</figcaption></figure></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><figure id=\"attachment_1132076\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1132076\" style=\"width: 800px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"wp-image-1132076\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Screenshot-2020-06-06-at-15.16.17-e1591712531822.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"500\" /><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1132076\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">YOAST held a quiz during their session, which involved a lot of laughter and was thoroughly enjoyed by us.</figcaption></figure></p>\n<h2>The talks and speakers</h2>\n<p>Two tracks were dedicated to the speakers and their talks both on Friday and Saturday. The talks ranged from topics including GDPR, accessibility, dark mode, project management, and WordPress coding. But no doubt most people tuned in to see Matt Mullenweg on Friday evening in a down-to-earth Q&amp;A session with Mattias.</p>\n<p><iframe title=\"WordCamp Europe 2020 Online Track 1 (Friday)\" width=\"1140\" height=\"641\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/df3Nx1vyswU?start=16235&#038;feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n<p>Watch the Q&amp;A session here again that starts with a demo of the latest Gutenberg developed features that are coming out soon.<br />\n<a href=\"https://2020.europe.wordcamp.org/schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The schedule</a> is up on the website and you can follow the links to any of the talks and watch them again on <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCaYQGYDpXpU4A17kxN-AgJQ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">YouTube</a>.</p>\n<p>We normally give you a list of notable speakers you should watch again, but this is so difficult to choose from. Of the talks I watched, every one has some valuable advice or gives you some food for thought.</p>\n<p>Track 2 on Friday is one of those line-ups that included talks that look beyond WordPress and what it is today. Like Miriam Schwab&#8217;s talk about cutting-edge development or David Lockie who talks about using AI in WordPress. Also, on track one about &#8216;WordPress performance trends&#8217; by Hristo Pandjarov is something that people have to deal with at some point. So trust us, take a look and skip through the talks for something that grabs your interest.</p>\n<h2>The experience as an attendee</h2>\n<p>Many of us at YITH joined in with some of the talks and presentations, but from a personal view as an attendee, I have a few comments.<br />\nKnowing that you can watch the talks days later, is a great comfort. Initially, the times clashed with family life as for example watching Matt Mullenweg&#8217;s talk was not what my kids had in mind as a Friday-evening treat with popcorn.<br />\nWhilst I communicated with as many fellow sponsors and attendees as possible, I could not manage to view the talks at the same time either, so having them available instantly in the hours and days after the event is a great way.</p>\n<p>What most of us missed was the interaction with friends and fellow WordPressers like you do at a &#8216;normal&#8217; WordCamp. Even the digital Zoom rooms do not make up for it, though great fun. Many attendees were reluctant to enter &#8216;sponsor booths&#8217; which is completely understandable. This is something very new and unusual but who knows this will be the norm in the future.</p>\n<p>After every WordCamp is it usual to digest all the information the days afterward in your mind, as each experience is very intense in a good way with lots of inspiration. Something that didn&#8217;t happen to me following a virtual event, but instead there is so much more to gain in the days and weeks ahead and we&#8217;d encourage you to watch the talks again, contact sponsors and engage in conversations or ask questions.</p>\n<p><img class=\"wp-image-1132091 aligncenter\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Screenshot-2020-06-06-at-19.51.55-e1591715735417.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"500\" /></p>\n<p>And finally&#8230; Thank you to the amazing organizers for keeping such a tight schedule and all tracks, rooms, sponsor areas flowing throughout the event. It is so easy to get it wrong, but you did great. There is only one more thing to say. We really hope to see you for real at the next WordCamp Europe in Porto in 2021.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/yit-news/wordcamp-europe-2020-a-very-smooth-virtual-experience/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\